const americanStories = [
  { id:'strange-behaviours', title:'Strange Behaviours', order:1, chars:['Ashley Taylor','Mary Taylor','Robert Taylor','Rachel Cohen (mentioned)','Brian (shrunken)','Megan Sanders (shrunken)','Timothy Walker (shrunken)'], desc:'The first American Setting story, told from dual perspectives: primarily from Brian, a shrunken vorarephile, and secondarily from Ashley Taylor herself. Brian is trapped in a Vortex box on Ashley\'s desk in her room, watching in horror and arousal as she casually snacks on the other shrinkies while studying German. The story culminates in Brian\'s unusual request and the graphic account of his death by digestion. Ashley\'s parents Mary and Robert are introduced, with a background argument hinting at Mary\'s moral objections to Vortex.' },
  { id:'an-american-nightmare', title:'An American Nightmare', order:2, chars:['Ashley Taylor','Mary Taylor','Robert Taylor','Max (shrunken)','Kayla Hayes','Megan Smith','Kelly Lewis','Ulrike Grimm','Alfred Hoffmann'], desc:'Max, a German student opposed to VortexFoods™, meets Ashley Taylor at an airport. He is arrested for drug possession and handed to Vortex operatives under "Section V", shrunk, and placed into the in-flight catering supply of the very plane Ashley boards. The story follows Max\'s terror inside the catering trolley, witnessing Kelly Lewis eat Thilo Busch, and his ultimate fate — swallowed unknowingly by Ashley during the in-flight promotional dinner. Ashley never learns the truth.' },
  { id:'a-matter-of-principle', title:'A Matter of Principle', order:3, chars:['Paige Wright (shrunken)','Dylan (shrunken)','Jordan (shrunken)','Miguel (shrunken)','Tyler (shrunken)','Diane (shrunken)','Kayla Hayes','Seo-Yun Park','Mark Campbell','Rachel Cohen','Ashley Taylor','Hannah Lindquist','Maria Reyes Ortega'], desc:'The most politically charged story in the American Setting. Paige Wright and her brother Dylan, along with around a dozen comrades including Jordan, Miguel, and Tyler, stage a night raid on one of Vortex\'s largest North American processing centres. Their mission is sabotaged from within — their embedded comrade Seo-Yun Park is revealed to be a Vortex informant — and the group is captured by Kayla Hayes and her paramilitary detail. Rather than face a trial, they are sent to processing and shrunken. Paige, Dylan, Jordan, and others end up in a Vortex display counter at a beachfront restaurant. The story\'s second half follows Hannah Lindquist, an incoming college freshman, as she eats her first ever shrinkie — with Paige becoming Hannah\'s first victim, swallowed whole after an intense internal moral struggle that turns out to be arousal rather than conscience. Rachel Cohen, meanwhile, eats Miguel and nearly eats Paige herself. Ashley Taylor swallows Dylan after learning who he is. The story ends with Hannah sleeping contentedly as her body digests her first dozen victims.' },
  { id:'good-for-goodness-sake', title:"Good for Goodness' Sake", order:4, chars:['Hannah Lindquist','Victoria Lindquist','William Lindquist','Ryan Lindquist','Arthur (shrunken)'], desc:"The fourth American Setting story, set entirely on Christmas Eve and Christmas Day in the Lindquist family's snowy hometown near the Canadian border. Hannah returns home after months at university during which she has consumed hundreds of shrinkies and is now a seasoned, sexually experienced predator. She buys a small box of shrinkies at the airport to snack on during her journey. Back in her old room, she empties them onto her mother's Christmas cookie plate and begins eating. Her older sister Victoria barges in and casually helps herself to around a dozen without a second thought, accidentally biting down on one tucked inside a piece of gingerbread and swallowing it with mild surprise. Hannah then recognises Arthur — a former classmate with a long-standing crush on her — among the remaining tinies. The story shifts to dual perspective as Arthur's dawning hope and Hannah's equally dawning predatory arousal are explored in parallel. Rather than spare him, Hannah inserts him into her vagina and uses him through an intense orgasm, then carries him inside her through Christmas Eve dinner with the entire family. Late that night she retrieves him, conducts a brief, final conversation, and swallows him whole while climaxing. The story's concluding pages follow Arthur's digestion in graphic physiological detail through the night, ending with his remains flushed away Christmas morning. The title references the Christmas carol 'Santa Claus is Coming to Town,' which plays in the background as Hannah swallows Arthur." },
  { id:'checking-out', title:'Checking Out', order:5, chars:['Victoria Lindquist','Cassandra Davis','Checking Out Main Character (shrunken)','Hannah Lindquist','Nicole Barnes (shrunken)','Scott Chapman (shrunken)','Marcus Chen (shrunken)','Harper Bennett (shrunken)','Monica Baker (shrunken)','Alex Baker (shrunken)','Joe Gunderson (shrunken)','Kyle Edwards (shrunken)'], desc:'A second-person story set in a Midwestern city hotel during a February snowstorm. The protagonist — a middle-aged male business traveller addressed as "you" — is woken at 6 AM by Victoria Lindquist\'s warm voice for his checkout call. He showers, packs, and heads down to the empty lobby, sharing a genuine mutual flirtation with Victoria across the front desk before heading to the parking garage. There he is stunned with a cattle prod by a Vortex operative in a black van and wakes up already shrunken inside a Vortex box in the hotel staff room. The story interweaves four perspectives: the protagonist inside the box, recognising Cassandra Davis and watching her eat Joe Gunderson with her morning coffee; Victoria processing her checkout and heading home with the box; Hannah on a dawn video call casually eating Monica and Alex Baker in spoonfuls of fruity loops cereal; and Cassandra eating through the rest of the staff box on her break. Victoria eats Nicole Barnes in an elevator on the way to her car. At home she runs a lavender-scented bath and drinks hot chocolate, eating Scott Chapman, Marcus Chen, and Harper Bennett one by one. The protagonist attempts to escape with the help of a fellow shrinkie who scales the dividing wall — Victoria snatches them both, swallows the other man, and when the protagonist falls free into the bath, she submerges and erupts from beneath him in a shark-dive (a move she learned from Stacy), sweeping him into her mouth with the bathwater. She swallows immediately, grimaces at the soapy taste, thumps her chest. She eats one more shrinkie to prevent escape, then shelves the remaining box — including Kyle Edwards, who watches his brother die before him — and goes to bed. The protagonist is digested overnight and flushed at 11 PM when Victoria uses the staff toilet before her next shift. Kyle survives two more days before being given to Stacy.' },
];

